<subSubSection pageId="21" pageNumber="22" type="nomenclature">
<paragraph pageId="21" pageNumber="22">
<taxonomicName authority="Sirenko, 2015" authorityName="Sirenko" authorityYear="2015" class="Polyplacophora" family="Leptochitonidae" genus="Leptochiton" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="Leptochiton macleani" order="Pholadomyoida" pageId="21" pageNumber="22" phylum="Mollusca" rank="species" species="macleani">Leptochiton macleani Sirenko, 2015</taxonomicName>
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection pageId="21" pageNumber="22" type="materials_examined">
<paragraph pageId="21" pageNumber="22">Material examined.</paragraph>
<paragraph pageId="21" pageNumber="22">NHM_446 NHMUK 20170073.1-2, collected 2013-10-20, 13.86367 -116.54432, 4050 m. http://data.nhm.ac.uk/object/d69b581d-8a79-4c4d-8f70-88b2ec07d86e</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection pageId="21" pageNumber="22" type="description">
<paragraph pageId="21" pageNumber="22">Description.</paragraph>
<paragraph pageId="21" pageNumber="22">
The form and pattern of tegmental granules together with the three aesthete pores are most similar to the images of 
<taxonomicName class="Polyplacophora" family="Leptochitonidae" genus="Leptochiton" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="Leptochiton macleani" order="Lepidopleurida" pageId="21" pageNumber="22" phylum="Mollusca" rank="species" species="macleani">Leptochiton macleani</taxonomicName>
(Sirenko, 2015: figs 34-36). Voucher NHM_446 length approx 10 mm, width 3.2 mm (Fig. 21).
</paragraph>
<caption pageId="21" pageNumber="22">
<paragraph pageId="21" pageNumber="22">
Figure 21. 
<taxonomicName class="Polyplacophora" family="Leptochitonidae" genus="Leptochiton" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="Leptochiton macleani" order="Lepidopleurida" pageId="21" pageNumber="22" phylum="Mollusca" rank="species" species="macleani">Leptochiton macleani</taxonomicName>
Sirenko, 2015. NHM_446 voucher specimen. A Live specimen (lateral view) after recovery from the ROV scoop sample B Preserved specimen (ventro-lateral view) following DNA extraction C Dorsal view D surface detail E SEM of tegmentum surface and pores. Scale bars: 4 mm (A); 0.5 mm (D); 0.3 mm (E). Image attribution Glover, Taylor, Ikebe, Dahlgren &amp; Wiklund, 2017.
</paragraph>
</caption>
</subSubSection>
